CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 7, 1958, pg. B5, reads: "Aspiring Artists - The five grade 8A students of Rogers School pose at a bulletin board display of work they have done in other fields.  It is a recent project in the art room consisting of linoleum block prints.  From left to right, they are Paul LeClere, Barbara Moore, John Greer, Sandra Lando and Joe Eubanks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rogers School students Paul LeClere, Barbara Moore, John Greer, Sandra Lando, and Joe Eubanks standing in front of bulletin board with display of stencils and block prints
